## How to wipe a hard drive using 'DD' and simultaniously being able to check the progress...

## using Ctrl F1 + F2 to switch between terminals
## tty1 and tty2
## In tty2 the command needs to be run everytime to see the current status

# tty1

sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/"insert dev here' bs=1m

# tty2

sudo kill -usr1 $(grep ^dd)
